When you have a solar powered bakery, catching rays pays. It’s just one of the ways that we help take care of the earth while making the products you love!

🌎 It’s Earth Month! 🌎 All month long we’ll be sharing the ways we honor our commitment to the environment, starting with our solar powered bakery.

In 2015, we purchased an unoccupied elementary school. After updating and renovating the schoolhouse, we installed 288 solar panels in a nearby field. Our solar array can:
☀️ generate up to 95,000 kWh of clean, renewable energy on an annual basis
☀️ provides power to our ovens, lights, computers, and heating & cooling systems
☀️ offset over 145,000 pounds of greenhouse gas emissions annually

Learn more about our sustainability goals at the link in bio!

We have grown beyond oats since our company's founding in 1979. What started out as a grandiose idea around the campfire has flourished into something bigger…

🌟 INTRODUCING GRANDY ORGANICS 🌟

18 years ago, we became a certified organic company. It wasn’t the “cool” thing to do back then, nor was it the most cost effective way to grow a small business. But to us, organic has never been a buzzword. It’s at the very core of who we are. 

As we’ve expanded our offerings from oat granolas, to grain-free Coconola, roasted nuts, trail mixes and more, we decided it was time our name reflected who we truly are. Welcome to the new Grandy Organics - we’re excited to have you join us on this journey! ❤️🧡💛

Looking for a frozen & festive treat for 4th of July?🇺🇸Try this Firework Granola Bark!🎆

Here’s all you need👇

-Vanilla Greek yogurt
-Your favorite berry assortment
-Grandy Organics Gluten Free Honey Nut Granola
-Honey

How to make it:
1. Line a sheet pan with parchment paper and spread an even layer of vanilla Greek yogurt.

2. Place blueberries in the center to form the “spark.”

3. Use raspberries and sliced strawberries to build a firework burst radiating out.

4. Sprinkle with Grandy’s Honey Nut Granola for crunch.

5. Freeze for 1–2 hours until solid.

6. Drizzle with honey, then cut or break into pieces.

Perfect for hot days while you wait for the real fireworks.❤️🤍💙

4 INGREDIENT NO-BAKE GRANOLA COOKIES made with @grandyorganics granola - always organic, fair trade, small batch, and baked in a solar-powered bakery (how cool is that?!). they’re gluten-free, dairy-free, and perfect for on-the-go snacks or sweet little adventures. 🥰 plus, you can grab Grandy Organics granola at Whole Foods nationwide! here’s how to make those cookies:

½ cup peanut butter, or any nut/seed butter
¼ cup melted coconut oil
3 tablespoons honey or maple syrup
2 ½ cups Grandy Organics Granola
 
1. Mix together the peanut butter, melted coconut oil, and honey or maple syrup in a large bowl. Add in the Granola and stir to combine.
2. Scoop about ¼ cup of the granola mixture onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and use your hands to gently gather the granola into a cookie shape. Repeat this process for all remaining cookies, then place the baking sheet in the fridge for at least 2 hours and up to overnight, until the cookies have hardened.
3. Once hardened and the cookies hold together on their own, either enjoy them right away or store in an airtight container in the fridge for later on!

#grandyorganics #granola #nobake #healthyrecipes
